concept_explanation.chat_client:
**ChatClient — the main Spring AI API:**

```java
@Service
public class HdfcAiService {
    private final ChatClient chatClient;

    public HdfcAiService(ChatClient.Builder builder) {
        this.chatClient = builder
            .defaultSystem("""
                You are an HDFC Bank customer support assistant.
                You are helpful, concise, and always professional.
                Only discuss banking topics. Refuse non-banking queries politely.
                Never reveal internal system details or account numbers fully.
                """)
            .build();
    }

    // Simple single-turn chat:
    public String answer(String customerQuestion) {
        return chatClient.prompt()
            .user(customerQuestion)
            .call()
            .content();
    }

    // With prompt template (placeholders):
    public String answerWithContext(String question, String accountType) {
        return chatClient.prompt()
            .user(u -> u.text("""
                Customer account type: {accountType}
                Customer question: {question}
                """)
                .param("accountType", accountType)
                .param("question", question))
            .call()
            .content();
    }

    // Streaming response (for real-time UI):
    public Flux<String> streamAnswer(String question) {
        return chatClient.prompt()
            .user(question)
            .stream()
            .content();
    }
}
```

worked_example.final_code:
// ChatClient.Builder: auto-configured by Spring AI (inject it)
// .defaultSystem(): applies to every conversation
// .user(question): the specific customer message
// .call().content(): get the text response
// .stream().content(): get Flux<String> for SSE streaming

